<h3 local-id=3D"06c90742b50f" id=3D"v2IndividualVerificationFlow-Security&a=
mp;Compliance">Security &amp; Compliance</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"0a2f1af8-c305-4a32-bb00-f82743d37198">
<li local-id=3D"73df78d3-03d6-4a66-83d5-b47a076858df">
<p local-id=3D"8cacf7c39823"><strong>PII in transit:</strong> TLS required =
for all communication between component, Interro backend, and host backend.=
</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e235e86a-77b3-4d27-9ac9-de283743cb9e">
<p local-id=3D"652f3d1724ee"><strong>PII at rest:</strong> SSNs, passport n=
umbers, and identity documents encrypted at rest in Interro's storage. Host=
 encrypts its retention copies using its own encryption pipeline.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ec1e2abf-daf4-4fe9-9132-0325c65e184b">
<p local-id=3D"40a7a8cc50a4"><strong>Document uploads:</strong> Handled dir=
ectly by the component to Interro infrastructure =E2=80=94 never routed thr=
ough the host frontend.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"daf1c978-1880-48d5-b561-342d44bb9813">
<p local-id=3D"7fe3316589fb"><strong>AML/OFAC screening:</strong> The indiv=
idual is screened against AML/OFAC watchlists. Results delivered via webhoo=
k.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"93e99f2f-18e9-477f-b7e3-213861aee3f6">
<p local-id=3D"2164adf541ef"><strong>Data retention:</strong> Host requires=
 retrieval access for a minimum of 10 years. If Interro purges data on a sh=
orter cycle, the host must be notified in advance.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"39c5ebde-64f6-421a-a9b1-8ef87867f1e8">
<p local-id=3D"c4b0df102971"><strong>Webhook security:</strong> HMAC signat=
ure verification, retry with backoff on delivery failure, idempotency keys.=
</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"965422268d7b"></p>
<p local-id=3D"ce38764fbdbe">Edits to v1 Individual FLow</p>
<ul local-id=3D"10f3a1198702">
<li local-id=3D"4dfa291c8ec4">
<p local-id=3D"2a9b22c7b188">Both KYC basic and KYC Complete</p>
<ul local-id=3D"f710529d7149">
<li local-id=3D"3b6b4914134f">
<p local-id=3D"f03a6ebe8dcc">There should be a flwo to have the user enter =
in their first and last name, date of birth, SSN / tax identifier for other=
 countries than the US. the SSN / tax id input should be masked with an opt=
ional =E2=80=9CShow=E2=80=9D button. this will be the first step after the =
user agrees to the agreements</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"375191fa42ba">
<p local-id=3D"dd28519c3d83">The collection of the address will be before t=
he Socure sdk initialization. keep the address collection screen general fl=
ow the same though, keep asking for the country.</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<ul local-id=3D"3564fe7c99b5">
<li local-id=3D"5f695eb213e2">
<p local-id=3D"871570df5265">KYC Basic</p>
<ul local-id=3D"a079f78d0a75">
<li local-id=3D"3f666c2d5bbc">
<p local-id=3D"e117d7ad3f11">KYC Basic will continue to have a document upl=
oad screen in the embeddable UI for ID. No Socure SDK.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"829851ac5945">
<p local-id=3D"1932a6d878d9">So the steps in step overview for KYC Basic wi=
ll be: 1. Provide Identity Information. 2. Provide Address information. 3. =
Provide Supplementary documents (if the application=E2=80=99s context id in=
dicates that supplementary documents must be uploaded). 4. Upload Identity =
Documents</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"671a09358061">
<p local-id=3D"8ef1531a6fe9">KYC Complete</p>
<ul local-id=3D"3cb20df10059">
<li local-id=3D"6b5d294d019e">
<p local-id=3D"21936a1ff8dd">KYC Complete will not have a document upload s=
creen in teh embeddable UI for ID. Instead, the embeddable UI will route to=
 the Socure SDK through Alloy through our KYC and risk review microservice.=
 The SDK will collect the ID through a scan or allow the user to upload doc=
umens. The Socure SDK will initiate a selfie.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"aaf1ec1402c2">
<p local-id=3D"be0fad1eb513">The Socure SDK will have a certain way of bein=
g initialized. There should be a slick looking screen that explains how it =
will work. there should be a centered header of =E2=80=9CIdentity Verificat=
ion=E2=80=9D. Then it should explain in steps: 1. Snap a photo of Id or upl=
oad it. 2. Take a selfie to verify identity. Then there should be a button =
to instantiate the SDK.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3c515e5ece26">
<p local-id=3D"51c074bdf58c">So the steps in the step overview for kyc comp=
lete should be: 1. Provide identity information. 2. provide address informa=
tion. 3. Provide Supplementary documents (if the application=E2=80=99s cont=
ext id indicates that supplementary documents must be uploaded). 4. Identit=
y Verification</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
    </div>
</body>
